&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role - Manufacturing Quality Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peak Energy is looking for a Manufacturing Quality Engineer to establish and lead quality engineering at Peak Energy from the ground up. The Manufacturing Quality Engineer will be responsible for establishing foundational quality systems, driving PFMEA and in-process quality controls, and managing supplier and incoming component quality. They will work closely with engineering, operations, and leadership to define the standards and processes that ensure our battery systems are safe, reliable, and ready for customer deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do (Responsibilities)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct rapid assessments of current build processes, failure modes, and risk areas, identifying the highest-priority gaps in quality and safety coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and continuously improve the PFMEA process with cross functional review and approval.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish an IQC framework, develop supplier qualification criteria, and begin laying the groundwork and systems for supplier quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with design and engineering to surface high-risk product failure modes early, bringing quality thinking into design reviews before issues become build problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define control, verification, and sampling plans to ensure part quality meets requirements in both development and on-going production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and track key quality metrics; drive corrective and preventive action (CAPA) processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate for quality in a fast-paced, production-driven environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the quality organization as the company scales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive field investigations and customer-facing quality responses.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
