&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role – Systems Modeling Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peak Energy is looking for a Systems Modeling Engineer to join our Energy Storage Systems (ESS) team and work at the forefront of the development of our gigawatt-scale energy storage systems. This role will leverage deep expertise to drive major thermal and electrical architectural decisions and dive into key electrical and battery component simulation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with design, test, validation, manufacturing engineering, and leadership to navigate our products&#39; development — exploring broadly and diving deeply with a drive for rigorous optimization, meticulous documentation, and clear communication of findings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a self-starter who is hungry for knowledge, holds themselves and others to high standards, and brings a get-it-done attitude to every challenge — big or small.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define system and component design direction and requirements by developing detailed models of battery energy storage systems across operating modes and external conditions, including battery modules and power electronic components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify key performance indicators and optimize system design to enhance these metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate models with experimental data and refine them based on test results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore broadly and deeply, and clearly communicate assumptions, inputs, and findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and spearhead selection and development of tools, infrastructure, and design practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface tightly with design, test, and validation partners to inform design decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive and participate in a culture of rapid prototyping and testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s or master&#39;s degree in Mechanical, Electrical, Systems Engineering, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5–10 years of experience working with power systems (non-academic)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with&lt;strong&gt; system-level&lt;/strong&gt; equivalent circuit models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong electrical and thermal engineering fundamentals&lt;/li&gt;
